                                                            for ones that can't access google drive: # IN THE CIRCUIT COURT FOR CHARLES COUNTY, MARYLAND

                                                            ## ADMINISTRATIVE ORDER 2025-05

                                                            **WHEREAS,** pursuant to Maryland Rule 16-105(b)(12), the Administrative Judge for Circuit Court for Charles County, Maryland is responsible for the overall administration of the Circuit Court, including taking needed steps to ensure the effective administration of the internal management of the court;

                                                            **WHEREAS,** Maryland courts have the inherent power to maintain *the safety and security* of those who are employed to work in the courthouse and *all who come to conduct court business*;

                                                            **WHEREAS,** the Respondent, Marvin D. Tutt ("Defendant"), has engaged *in a pattern of confrontational, intimidating, and threatening behavior towards staff and judicial officers of this Court* as described below; and

                                                            **WHEREAS,** it has been reported that on June 17, 2025, and June 19, 2025, the Respondent sent a series of emails with inappropriate communication to the Child Support Case Manager in the Family Services Department approximately six (6) times demanding *a change be made to the findings and recommendations*; and

                                                            **WHEREAS,** it has been reported to the undersigned that on July 27, 2025, July 28, 2025, July 29, 2025, September 13, 2025, September 14, 2025, and September 15, 2025, the *Respondent sent a series of emails directly* to the Child Support Case Manager in the Family Services Department and the language was inappropriate and threatening to staff, Family Magistrates, including referencing the murder of a Maryland Judge;

                                                            **WHEREAS,** it has been reported that on October 15, 2025, the Respondent appeared before Honorable Judge William R. Greer for a scheduled hearing, and at the conclusion of the hearing, the Respondent directly threatened Judge Greer, using the words "You are a fraud and I'm coming for you too.";

                                                            **WHEREAS,** it has been reported to the undersigned that on October 15, 2025, the Respondent sent numerous emails to the Child Support Case Manager in the Family Services Department expressing dissatisfaction with Judge Greer;

                                                            **IT IS THEREFORE,** this 27th day of October 2025, by the Circuit Court for Charles County, MD, hereby

                                                            **ORDERED** that the Respondent shall immediately cease *all harassment, intimidation, and threatening communication* to Court staff, including in person, by phone, by email, *and by regular mail*; and it is further

                                                            **ORDERED** that any papers or pleadings that the Respondent *intends to file with the Court* shall be made by filing with the Clerk of the Court; and it is further

                                                            **ORDERED** that the Respondent shall not have access to any Court facilities without the prior written notification and approval from the Charles County Sheriff's Office and Administrative Judge or Acting Administrative Judge; and it is further

                                                            **ORDERED** that notification must be made via first-class mail or via email: CCCharlesCtAdmin@mdcourts.gov and received at least three (3) business days in advance of *intent to visit the Circuit Court for Charles County, Maryland*; the notification must inform the *Charles County Sheriff's Office* of the specific date and time he intends to be on the property, *the reason for the visit*, and how long the visit is intended to take, which shall not be for more *than thirty (30) minutes* unless approved by the Administrative Judge; and

                                                            **ORDERED** that any request by the Respondent for specific permission to enter Court facilities shall be submitted to the Charles County Sheriff's Office - Court Security Division with approval and notification to the Administrative Judge or Acting Administrative Judge; and it is further

                                                            **ORDERED** that if Respondent is granted permission to enter Court facilities, he shall be escorted at all times by a Deputy of the Charles County Sheriff's Office; and it is further

                                                            **ORDERED** that any failure to comply with the terms of this Order may result in a finding of contempt.

                                                            ---

